The paper focuses on hyperparameter optimization for training neural networks, which is a core problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of compressed sensing techniques for orthogonal polynomials, which falls under the category of signal processing and information theory (cs.IT) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the sample complexity of learning decision trees, which is a topic in computational learning theory (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses experiments on training deep neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
